5-10 October 1992 -93something regarded as a normative example to be copied; archetype; exemplar. From Christopher Alexander’s work in architecture: A pattern is a solution to a problem in a context. Every pattern is a solution to a problem in a context. l A pattern has three parts: Problem, context, solution . A pattern offers workable solutions Patterns are rules of thumbs that can be used again and again-useful, practical “how to” guidelines. Patterns tend not to be domain-specific. Patterns are one of the primary mechanisms that people use for passing on expertise to others.